# Provider Page and State Page: Style and Structure (for Flask Replication)

This document describes the **style** and **structure** of the **Provider (facility)** page and **State** page as implemented in the Streamlit PBJ apps (`PBJ_Dashboard.py`, `Internal_PBJ_Dashboard.py`, `prov_info.py`), so you can replicate the same look and flow in a Flask app.

---

## 1. Source of Truth

| Page type   | Primary source        | Alternate / related              |
|------------|------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| **Provider** | `prov_info.py` → `show_facility_page()` | `PBJ_Dashboard.py` → facility-level branch in `display_metrics(level="Facility")` |
| **State**    | `PBJ_Dashboard.py` → `display_metrics(level="State")` | Same app: state selector, state-level metrics and charts |
| **PBJ Takeaway (facility)** | `PBJ_Dashboard.py` → `pbj_takeaway_card()` | Bordered summary card with chips + narrative; anchor `#pbj-takeaway` |
| **PBJ Takeaway (state)**   | `Internal_PBJ_Dashboard.py` → `state_pbj_takeaway_card()` | Same pattern for state-level summary |

---

## 2. Shared Style Tokens

Use these consistently in Flask (e.g. in `templates/dynamic_facility_dashboard.html` or a new template).

### Colors
- **Primary / header / links:** `#1976d2` (blue)
- **Secondary / description:** `#5a6c7d`, `#666`
- **Border / divider:** `#e3eaf3` (light blue-gray), `2.5px solid`
- **Background (header block):** `linear-gradient(135deg, #f8fafd 0%, #e3f2fd 100%)` or `#f8f9fa` for body
- **Chart bars:** Reported = blue; Case-Mix = red; Adjusted = green (dashed)
- **320 Consulting / branding:** `#1769aa`

### Typography
- **Section headers:** `font-size: 1.35em`, `font-weight: 700`, `color: #1976d2`, `letter-spacing: 0.01em`
- **Subheaders:** `st.subheader` → use Bootstrap `h4` or equivalent, bold
- **Caption / meta:** `font-size: 0.9em`, `color: #666`
- **Main app title:** `font-size: 2.6em`, `font-weight: 700`, `color: #1769aa`

### Spacing and layout
- **Section header:** `margin-top: 8px` (or `-30px` when directly under main header), `padding-bottom: 4px`, `border-bottom: 2.5px solid #e3eaf3`
- **Mobile:** `@media (max-width: 768px)` — reduce font sizes, hide/show desktop vs mobile text, add `.state-page-mobile-padding` (e.g. `margin-top: 15px`)
- **Desktop state page:** `.state-page-mobile-padding` → `margin-top: 25px`
- **Charts:** `margin: 20px 0`, container with `border: 1px solid #e9ecef`, `border-radius: 8px`, `padding: 20px`, light box-shadow

### CSS class to replicate (section header)
```css
.section-header {
  margin-top: 8px;
  font-size: 1.35em;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #1976d2;
  border-bottom: 2.5px solid #e3eaf3;
  padding-bottom: 4px;
  letter-spacing: 0.01em;
}
```

