## 3. Provider (Facility) Page — Structure

### 3.1 Data source
- **prov_info:** Single facility from `provider_info_combined.csv` filtered by CCN; rows by `processing_date`; quarter from mapping (e.g. `quarter_to_provider_mapping_examples.csv`).
- **PBJ_Dashboard facility level:** Facility-level metrics (e.g. from facility/state/national metrics CSVs or DuckDB), current quarter + previous quarter for deltas.

### 3.2 Page layout (top to bottom)

1. **Header block**
   - **Title:** Facility name (e.g. from `provider_name` or `PROVNAME`) + optional quarter, e.g. `{Provname} ({Quarter name})`.
   - **Subtitle line:** `City, State • Ownership type` (caption-style).
   - **Optional (PBJ_Dashboard):** Second line with county, link to state page (`?state=XX`), and “Ownership:” link to entity page (`?entity=ID`) or “N/A”.
   - **Style:** `.section-header` as above; subtitle `font-size: 0.9em`, `color: #666`, `margin-top: 4px`.

2. **Quarter selector**
   - **prov_info:** Single selectbox: “Quarter (staffing data)” — options = sorted quarters for that facility; default = latest.
   - Use selected quarter to filter all staffing charts and tables below.

3. **Charts (order and type)**
   - **Reported vs Case-Mix (single quarter):** Grouped bar chart (Total, RN, CNA). Blue = Reported, Red = Case-Mix. Delta annotations above bars (Δ HPRD and %). Title: “Reported vs. Case-Mix (Expected)” + facility name + quarter.
   - **Methodology blurb:** Short italic text under chart (case-mix definition, positive/negative delta meaning).
   - **Ratings methodology:** In an expander/collapsible: “Ratings Methodology & Footnotes” (star ratings, footnote codes 1, 2, 6, 9, 10, 12, 13, 14, 18, 19).
   - **Total Staffing longitudinal:** Line chart by quarter — Reported Total (blue), Case-Mix Total (red), Adjusted Total (green, dashed). X = quarter labels (e.g. “Q1 2021”), Y = HPRD.
   - **RN Staffing longitudinal:** Same idea for RN (Reported / Case-Mix / Adjusted).
   - **CNA (NA) longitudinal:** Same for NA/CNA.
   - **Ratings over time:** Line chart — Overall, Staffing, Health Inspection ratings by quarter (if available).
   - Chart height: ~280 (single-quarter bar), ~400 (longitudinal). Use `plotly_white` template; legend horizontal, above chart (`y=1.02`).

4. **Ownership change**
   - **Subheader:** “Ownership Change History”
   - If any `provider_changed_ownership_in_last_12_months == "Y"`: table of processing date, category, value.
   - Else: short message “No evidence of ownership changes found.”

5. **Basic facility information**
   - **Subheader:** “Basic Facility Information”
   - Optional toggle: “Show basic facility information” (default on).
   - Table: Provider Name, City, State, County, Ownership Type, For Profit, Overall/Staffing/Health Inspection Rating, Matched Quarter, Latest Processing Date. One row (latest record).

6. **Complete facility data table**
   - **Subheader:** “Complete Facility Data by Quarter”
   - **Caption:** “All available data for this facility across all quarters”
   - Wide table: Month/Year, Data Release Date, quarter, avg_residents_per_day, ratings, reported/case_mix/adjusted HPRD (Total, RN, LPN, NA), weekend HPRD, turnover, ownership change. Numeric columns formatted to 3 decimals.
   - Sorted by Data Release Date descending.
   - Optional fixed height (e.g. 400px) with scroll.

7. **Summary statistics (bottom)**
   - **Label:** “Summary Statistics:”
   - **Columns:** e.g. 3 columns: Total Records, Quarters Covered | Latest Overall Rating, Latest Staffing Rating | (optional third column).
   - Display as small metrics/cards.

### 3.3 Provider page — Components to replicate in Flask
- One main content column (optionally narrow right column for future use).
- HTML: header (h1/h2) + subtitle `<p>` or `<div>` with same classes.
- Quarter dropdown → send selection to backend; return JSON for charts or render server-side.
- Plotly charts: same trace names and colors; same layout (title, axis labels, legend).
- Tables: Bootstrap table or similar; optional “Show basic info” via checkbox + JS or server round-trip.
- Expander: Bootstrap collapse or `<details>` for “Ratings Methodology & Footnotes”.
- Horizontal rules (`<hr>` or `st.markdown("---")` equivalent) between major sections.

