## 5. PBJ Takeaway Card — Style and Structure

The **PBJ Takeaway** is a compact, bordered summary card on **facility** and **state** pages: one-glance narrative (HPRD vs state/case-mix or national, trend, and “put another way” staff counts). Replicate it in Flask so provider and state pages keep the same “brief” experience.

### 5.1 Where it appears and anchor

- **Facility / State page:** Card near the top of the content. Use **`id="pbj-takeaway"`** on the card wrapper so the floating button can jump to it.
- **Floating button:** Fixed (e.g. `top: 80px; right: 18.5px; z-index: 1000`). Label: **“PBJ Takeaway”** (desktop), **“PBJ Brief”** (mobile). Link: `#pbj-takeaway`. Style: gradient `#1976d2` → `#42a5f5`, white text, rounded pill, arrow “→”. Optional: fade/hide after delay via JS.

### 5.2 Container and title row

- **Container:** Bordered box; padding; position relative if you use an absolute badge.
- **Title row:** Flex, align center. Optional: PBJ icon 24×24px, then **“PBJ Takeaway: {facility name}”** or **“PBJ Takeaway: {state name}”**. Title: `font-size: 16px`, `font-weight: bold`, `margin-bottom: 10px`.

### 5.3 Chip (pill) style

- **Base:** `display: inline-block`, `padding: 2px 8px`, `border-radius: 999px`, `font-weight: 600`, `font-size: 0.85rem`, `margin-right: 6px`.
- **Tones:** good `#065f46`/`#ecfdf5`, warn `#7c2d12`/`#fff7ed`, neutral `#334155`/`#f1f5f9`.
- **Special:** High Risk = red `#dc2626` bg (facility, when `is_high_risk`). Ownership Change = amber `#fef3c7`/`#92400e` (facility). Entity link = blue pill linking to entity page. State page: optional “State Standard: X HPRD” chip from MACPAC.

### 5.4 Facility PBJ Takeaway — Content order

1. Title: “PBJ Takeaway: {Facility Name}”.
2. **Chips:** High Risk (if any) → Total HPRD (📈/📉) → {State} HPRD → Census → Contract → Ownership type → Entity (link) → Ownership Change (if any).
3. **Narrative:** “**{Facility}**’s reported **{X.XX} hours per resident day** (≈ {Y.Y} residents per total staff) in {Quarter}{trend}{census trend}. This level is {above/below/around} the {State} ratio of {state_hprd} and {above/below/around} its case-mix (expected) {casemix_hprd}.” (If no case-mix: “… CMS did not report case-mix data …”.)
4. **“Put another way…”:** “On a typical **30-bed floor** at {facility} you’d see about **{N} staff**, including ~{M} nurse aides. For the entire {census}-resident facility, that’s about {total_staff} total staff, including ~{aides} nurse aides.”
5. *Note: staffing varies by day and shift…*
6. **High-risk factors (if any):** “**⚠️ High-Risk Factors:** 1-Star, SFF, …”
7. **320 Consulting** badge (small, bottom-right of card).

**Inputs:** facility name, reported_hprd, quarter_label, state_name, state_hprd, casemix_hprd, census, contract, trend_delta, census_trend, previous_year, ownership_type, affiliated_entity, affiliated_entity_id, high_risk_indicators, ownership_change.

### 5.5 State PBJ Takeaway — Content order

1. Title: “PBJ Takeaway: {State Name}”.
2. **Chips:** {State} HPRD (📈/📉) → National HPRD → State Rank (#k of n) → optional State Standard chip.
3. **Narrative:** “**{State}**’s reported **{X.XX} hours per resident day** (≈ {Y.Y} residents per total staff) in {Quarter}{trend}. This level is {above/below/around} the national ratio of {national_hprd} HPRD and ranks **#{rank}** out of {total_states} states.”
4. **“Put another way…”:** 30-bed floor + average {State} facility size staff/aide counts.
5. *Note:* same as facility.
6. **320 Consulting** badge.

**Inputs:** state_name, reported_hprd, quarter_label, national_hprd, state_rank, total_states, trend_delta, previous_year, aide_share, floor_beds (30), avg_facility_size (e.g. 100). Optional: state standard from MACPAC.

### 5.6 Flask replication notes

- Add `<div id="pbj-takeaway">` (or similar) around the card for the floating button link.
- Implement `_classify(reported, benchmark)` → “above”/“below”/“around” and `_fmt(val, decimals)` for numbers and trend/census sentences.
- Chips: HTML or a small component with label, value, tone, optional link.

