## 6. Replication Checklist for Flask

- [ ] **Colors / CSS:** Add `.section-header` and shared color variables (e.g. `#1976d2`, `#e3eaf3`, `#1769aa`) to your Flask template or static CSS.
- [ ] **Provider page:** Route (e.g. `/facility/<ccn>` or `/?facility=CCN`); template with header (name + quarter), quarter dropdown, Reported vs Case-Mix bar chart, longitudinal line charts (Total, RN, CNA), ratings chart, ownership table, basic info table, full data table, summary metrics.
- [ ] **State page:** Route (e.g. `/state/<code>` or `/?state=XX`); template with state section header, 4-metric row, then charts.
- [ ] **Charts:** Serve Plotly via `plotly.json` or `Plotly.newPlot` in JS; or server-side render to image. Keep same trace names and colors (blue/red/green).
- [ ] **Responsive:** Media query 768px; optional desktop/mobile text swap and state-page top padding.
- [ ] **Data:** Flask endpoints that return facility-level and state-level metrics (and quarters) so the templates or JS can drive the same structure as Streamlit (e.g. `/api/facility/<ccn>/metrics`, `/api/state/<code>/metrics`).
- [ ] **PBJ Takeaway:** Add `id="pbj-takeaway"` card (facility and state) with chips, narrative, “Put another way…”, note, and 320 badge; optional floating “PBJ Takeaway” / “PBJ Brief” button linking to `#pbj-takeaway`.

